From the host: "A deep dive into Brazil's burgeoning Funkhall scene - a fusion of baile funk production techniques and dancehall rhythmic structures - with a guest mix from one of the sounds true pioneers, Sao Paulo's DJ Thiago Martins."

From the host: "WELCOME 2 SYSTEM SEOUL"
The enigmatic polymath, producer and MC brbko takes over the NTS airwaves each month. Brak don't crack.
LA-based DJ and producer Introspekt delivers a monthly missive of UK garage, 2-step and more.

Croatian DIY label Low Income $quad showcase their catalogue and extended family of producers - Expect neo trance sounds, reworked Memphis rap acapellas, 90s-inspired fast techno and noisy experimentalism.
Producer and DJ Jay Donaldson, also known as Palms Trax, brings his selections to NTS' Channel 1 for a two-hour session every other month.

Artist, producer, label owner and DJ Lee Gamble bringing an oneiric bi-monthly show of current sound and music from his hallucinated musical continuum. Expect anything from Drill to Dream pop, Conceptual Sound and Jazz to bleached out rave memories..

nts2.d:
UK experimental folk and self-described “slacker trad” duo Milkweed create lo-fi folk soundscapes constructed around folklore collections and archaeological texts, their most recent project is built around the epic Irish tale Táin Bó Cuailnge.
They present a mix of original recordings, and traditional folk music from across Europe.

Chicago based DJ and collector Cameron Chapleau dives into the world of fanzine flexi singles from the UK in the late ‘80s and ‘90s. Flexi-singles are thin vinyl pressings that could be produced at low cost, and often used for promotional releases, especially in the DIY indie, punk and hardcore scenes.

Andy Butler from Hercules & Love Affair joins us once a month to showcase his diverse record collection.
From the host: "VITIGRRL is a Chicago-born selector whose sound bridges the city’s storied house lineage with abundant, raw, pulse-driven energy. Her name tells the story: VITI honors her roots and heritage, while GRRL embodies untamed feminine power, creative rebellion and defiant joy."

Founded in 1988 by Toronto producers Nick Fiorucci and Andrew Komis, Bigshot operated for just two years — but in that brief window released a run of records that would deeply shape the emerging sound of UK rave and permanently alter the trajectory of dance music.
Dark, moody, and ferociously funky, the Bigshot sound linked Toronto to the nascent scenes of Chicago, Detroit, New York, and the Midwest. Alongside Ron Allen and Len Grant, Fiorucci and Komis fused house, techno, electro, garage, and freestyle into a signature mix of snapping 808s, FM basslines, 303 pressure, dubwise mixing, and blistering vocals. This is the sound of Toronto house.
Words and selections by Tony Price.
Lesser heard sounds with a focus on femmes in punk from artist and musician Sara A.

nts2.n: CONFUSING MIX W/ JOSH DA COSTA
nts2.d: Lock in for a monthly transmission of leftfield sonics from Josh Da Costa live from LA.

Tana Yonas collects songs like souvenirs, each recalling precious moments found leafing through dusty foreign record shops or catching sonic fragments weathered by time from the radio of bumpy taxi rides. Listen as she delicately guilds together these memories and shares music from lesser known and under represented musical traditions from across the globe and decades.
From the host: "This January mix leans into quiet, patient, and deeply textured environments, pulling together fragments of jazz, folk, spirituals, and ambient music."
NZ avant-folk artist Maxine Funke returns to NTS, helping mark the release of her new record “Timeless Town”, playing a suite of meditative folk and original recordings.
Explorations in everything from krautrock and dub to jungle and techno once a month.
Past, present and future soundtracks from Beirut to Bangkok via Bombay.
What are the prerequisites for Senay Kenfe and his 2 hour bi-monthly show playing only heat. Chase the Quiet Storm, live and direct from the LA Studio.

PPU signed vocalist & producer dreamcastmoe transmits a monthly program directly from LA via DC..
From the host: "This months Dreamcastmoe Show feat. Valentina - Valentina is a Chicanx community organizer and DJ for over 15 years currently residing in Baltimore. Digging in their favorite record stores they have curated an arsenal of the obscure, evocative, and important to serve dance floors with their all vinyl sets crafting their brujeria of sound, held heavily in their culture and being."

subtle.d: Established in 2013, eatmybeat is a hybrid record label & club brand that was brought together by a group of friends with a passion for electronic music and building community. With diverse tastes, they support and champion the underground bass music scene through events and releases on the label. Refusing to be pigeonholed into a specific sound, they showcase everything from hip-hop, bass & breaks, through to techno, jungle, dubstep and grime. As long as it's tasty and full fat, you best believe eatmybeat are snacking on it.
Born in Sunderland, based in London, Kitschko's productions and selections display a deep appreciation of UK club culture, and an affinity for late night, introspective sounds.

As a drummer since childhood, Chacho has always had an insatiable appetite for new and unique beats.
Combining his love of global percussion, dark grooves and deeper low end frequencies, 
his sets feature a blend of dubstep, grime, garage, breaks, hip hop and other flavours from around the world.
Hailing from Belfast but making moves in Nottingham, Nikki O is a DJ and radio presenter whose sets blend 4/4 rhythms, breakbeats, and the bassier side of techno.
